This paper deals with the problem of privacy-preserving data sharing, which is a topic that falls under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new notion of differential privacy, which is a concept that is closely related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely categories for this paper are cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
